      <abstract>In 1903, the Watchung Congregational Church emerged out of the need for a
        Congregational church around Watchung, New Jersey. This collection contains records from the
        church's inception onward including vital statistics, historical information, and
        administrative records. On March 12, 1974, an electrical fire destroyed the sanctuary
        building, eventually resulting in a decision to dissolve the Watchung Congregational Church.
        Most members moved to the Union Congregational Church or the First Congregational Church,
        both in Montclair. When the property was sold in 1977, the proceeds of the sale went to
        those two congregations.</abstract>
